---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { EMAIL, GITHUB_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Base title="Work with me" description="Freelance: auditable RAG systems, LLM cost control, backend .NET that holds.">
  <h1>Work with me</h1>
  <img class="portrait" src="/portrait.jpg" alt="Serhiy Kucherenko" width="112" height="112" loading="lazy" />
  <p>Three problems I take on:</p>

  <h2>Your AI answers need to be auditable</h2>
  <p>
    RAG that cites the exact page, and evals that catch regressions before your users do. I
    built <a href="https://github.com/KucherenkoSerhiy/payments-rag">payments-rag</a> this
    way: every answer carries its source, and a cross-model judge grades the output.
  </p>

  <h2>Your LLM bill needs to stop surprising you</h2>
  <p>
    Caching, spend tracking, and knowing what a feature costs per request before finance
    asks. I'm building a gateway for exactly this problem, in the open.
  </p>

  <h2>Your .NET backend needs to hold</h2>
  <p>
    Nine years of it, much of that in banking infrastructure, where "mostly works" doesn't
    count as working.
  </p>

  <p>
    How I work, in one story: <a href="/blog/localhost-trap/">a 10-second mystery, measured down to a one-word fix</a>&#32;(10,137 ms → 27 ms).
  </p>
  <p>
    How it starts: you write me a paragraph about the problem. If I can help, we talk. If I
    can't, I say so and, when I can, point you at someone who can.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a> · <a href={GITHUB_URL}>the code speaks too</a>
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: right;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
